executor_display_name: View Product Concept by RxNorm Concept ID (RXCUI)
executor_description: This returns a list of product concepts which have been mapped to the provided RXCUI. The relationship between RXCUI and DrugBank product concepts is many-to-many. If the specified RXCUI is not understood, or has not yet been imported into DrugBank, then a 404 error will be raised. If the RXCUI is understood, but the specified RxNorm concept is not considered equivalent to any DrugBank product concept, then an empty array will be returned. This API supports pagination, although results will rarely, if ever be paginated with the default per-page setting of 50 results per page.

pathParams.description: The RXCUI of the RxNorm concept for which to retrieve product concepts.

queryParams.description: If set to include, includes product concepts for which all products have been withdrawn. If set to true, includes only product concepts for which all products have been withdrawn. If set to false, includes only product concepts with at least one non-withdrawn product.
If set to true, include simple descriptions for the product concept ingredients.
If set to true, include clinical descriptions for the product concept ingredients.
